quotation: in africa, this earthquake was felt almost as severely as it had been in europe. a great part of the city of algiers was destroyed. many houses were thrown down at fez and mequinez, and multitudes were buried beneath their ruins. similar effects were realized in morocco. its effects were likewise felt at tangier, at tetuan, at funchal in the island of madeira;... it is probable... that all africa was shaken by this tremendous convulsion. at the north, it extended to norway and sweden; germany, holland, france, great britain, and ireland were all more or less agitated by the same great and terrible commotion of the elements.
speaker: sir charles

quotation: Algiers was essentially the epicenter of revolutionary ideas for people attempting to throw off colonialism,
speaker: Bouchra Khalili
